---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Ornament from '~/components/ui/Ornament.astro';
import Badge from '~/components/ui/Badge.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="S/V Nomine Carens"
  description="The S/V Nomine Carens — a 2007 Catalina 309 sloop, berthed in Carrabelle, Florida. The sail-driven vessel of the Miccosukee Yacht Club."
  active="about"
>

  <section class="vessel-header">
    <div class="container">
      <a href="/#fleet" class="back-link">&larr; The Fleet</a>
      <div class="vessel-badges">
        <Badge tone="navy">Sail &middot; Catalina 309</Badge>
        <Badge tone="paper">2007</Badge>
        <Badge tone="paper">Carrabelle, FL</Badge>
      </div>
      <h1>S/V Nomine Carens</h1>
      <p class="lead vessel-lead">
        The Club's sail-driven vessel. A 2007 Catalina 309 sloop, berthed at the Carrabelle
        waterfront. Cruising World Boat of the Year, 2007. Name pending committee formation.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="vessel-photo-full">
    <img src="/assets/nomine-carens.jpg" alt="S/V Nomine Carens at the dock in Carrabelle" />
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="narrow">

      <h2>The Vessel</h2>
      <p>
        The Catalina 309 is the work of designer Gerry Douglas, who took the legendary Catalina
        30 &mdash; one of the most produced cruising sailboats in American history &mdash; added
        roughly a foot of length and eight inches of beam, and produced something reviewers called
        "the big small boat." Cruising World named it Boat of the Year in 2007, including top
        overall domestic boat. Approximately 200 to 300 were built between 2005 and 2012.
        The Club's example is a 2007 model.
      </p>
      <p>
        The 309 is classed as a serious cruiser in a daysailor's footprint. Her beam gives the
        cabin more space than the length suggests. The cockpit is described by reviewers as
        "vast" &mdash; a six-footer finds ample legroom without contortion. Wide side decks with
        proper non-skid and inboard chainplates mean foredeck work does not require a prayer.
      </p>

      <Ornament />

      <h2>Under Sail</h2>
      <p>
        The 309's distinguishing feature is her in-mast furling mainsail, which draws skepticism
        from sailors who regard it as insufficiently serious and praise from everyone who has
        actually sailed with one. Reefing is a matter of releasing the outhaul and pulling a
        loop; the sail rolls inside the mast. The boat responds quickly to trim changes and
        communicates what works. Hull speed is 6.9 knots. She has been recorded at nearly
        7 knots sustained while carrying half mainsail and half jib.
      </p>
      <p>
        In winds to 15 knots, sheets can be trimmed without winch assistance. The traveler
        controls sit on the port coachroof, within easy reach of the helm. She tacks through
        approximately 85 degrees and accelerates cleanly out of the turn. The wing keel &mdash;
        drawing 4'4" &mdash; allows access to shallower anchorages than the fin-keel variant
        and suits the Gulf Coast sailing grounds where she operates.
      </p>

      <Ornament />

      <h2>Below Decks</h2>
      <p>
        The forward V-berth is properly sized, with a large deck hatch for ventilation and
        adequate headroom for sitting. Storage lockers are numerous and include a hanging
        locker. The saloon seats four at the table comfortably; the table drops to form
        additional berth space. The U-shaped galley provides a two-burner stove, counter
        space, and a refrigerator that runs on AC or DC.
      </p>
      <p>
        The aft cabin accommodates two, though not elaborately. Engine access is excellent:
        the companionway step swings clear to expose three sides of the Yanmar diesel.
        The 309 came from the factory with air-conditioning ductwork already run, which
        is not a luxury in Florida waters and speaks well of the designers' practical
        sense.
      </p>

      <Ornament />

      <h2>On the Name</h2>
      <p>
        The vessel is registered under the provisional designation <em>Nomine Carens</em>,
        Latin for "lacking a name," pending the first meeting of the Club's Naming Committee.
        The Committee does not yet exist. Captain Joly has expressed no urgency in the matter,
        which the Club considers a position of dignity rather than oversight.
      </p>

    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-paper">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="specs-header">
        <span class="eyebrow-rule">Technical Register</span>
        <h2>Specifications</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="specs-grid">
        <div class="specs-group">
          <div class="specs-group-label">Dimensions</div>
          <dl>
            <div class="spec-row"><dt>LOA</dt><dd>32' 9"</dd></div>
            <div class="spec-row"><dt>LWL</dt><dd>26' 6"</dd></div>
            <div class="spec-row"><dt>Beam</dt><dd>11' 6"</dd></div>
            <div class="spec-row"><dt>Draft (wing keel)</dt><dd>4' 4"</dd></div>
            <div class="spec-row"><dt>Draft (fin keel)</dt><dd>6' 3"</dd></div>
          </dl>
        </div>
        <div class="specs-group">
          <div class="specs-group-label">Weight & Sail</div>
          <dl>
            <div class="spec-row"><dt>Displacement</dt><dd>9,800 lbs</dd></div>
            <div class="spec-row"><dt>Ballast</dt><dd>4,000 lbs</dd></div>
            <div class="spec-row"><dt>Sail Area</dt><dd>523 sq ft</dd></div>
            <div class="spec-row"><dt>Hull Speed</dt><dd>6.9 kts</dd></div>
          </dl>
        </div>
        <div class="specs-group">
          <div class="specs-group-label">Mechanical</div>
          <dl>
            <div class="spec-row"><dt>Engine</dt><dd>Yanmar 3YM20</dd></div>
            <div class="spec-row"><dt>Power</dt><dd>21 hp diesel</dd></div>
            <div class="spec-row"><dt>Mainsail</dt><dd>In-mast furling</dd></div>
            <div class="spec-row"><dt>Designer</dt><dd>Gerry Douglas</dd></div>
            <div class="spec-row"><dt>Built</dt><dd>2005 &ndash; 2012</dd></div>
          </dl>
        </div>
        <div class="specs-group">
          <div class="specs-group-label">The Club's Vessel</div>
          <dl>
            <div class="spec-row"><dt>Year</dt><dd>2007</dd></div>
            <div class="spec-row"><dt>Captain</dt><dd>Rod Joly</dd></div>
            <div class="spec-row"><dt>Home Port</dt><dd>Carrabelle, FL</dd></div>
            <div class="spec-row"><dt>Name</dt><dd><em>Nomine Carens</em> (provisional)</dd></div>
          </dl>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
.vessel-header {
  background: var(--bg-deep);
  color: var(--fg-on-deep);
  padding-block: var(--space-9) var(--space-8);
}
.back-link {
  display: inline-block;
  font-family: var(--font-sans);
  font-size: 12px;
  font-weight: 600;
  letter-spacing: var(--tracking-wide);
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--brass-200);
  text-decoration: none;
  margin-bottom: var(--space-5);
  transition: color var(--dur-fast) var(--ease-out);
}
.back-link:hover { color: var(--sail-50); }
.vessel-badges { display: flex; gap: var(--space-2); margin-bottom: var(--space-4); flex-wrap: wrap; }
.vessel-header h1 {
  color: var(--sail-50);
  font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 5vw, var(--fs-display));
  margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
}
.vessel-lead {
  color: var(--fg-on-deep-muted);
  max-width: 58ch;
}

.vessel-photo-full {
  background: var(--navy-900);
  height: 480px;
  overflow: hidden;
}
.vessel-photo-full img {
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
  object-fit: cover;
  object-position: center 30%;
  opacity: 0.9;
}

.specs-header {
  text-align: center;
  margin-bottom: var(--space-7);
}
.specs-header h2 { margin-top: var(--space-4); }
.specs-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
  gap: var(--space-6);
}
.specs-group-label {
  font-family: var(--font-sans);
  font-size: var(--fs-overline);
  font-weight: 600;
  letter-spacing: var(--tracking-xwide);
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--brass-600);
  margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  padding-bottom: var(--space-3);
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
}
dl { margin: 0; }
.spec-row {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
  gap: var(--space-4);
  padding-block: 6px;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  font-size: 14px;
}
.spec-row:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
dt {
  font-family: var(--font-sans);
  font-weight: 500;
  color: var(--fg-muted);
}
dd {
  font-family: var(--font-mono);
  font-size: 13px;
  color: var(--fg);
  margin: 0;
  text-align: right;
}

@media (max-width: 900px) {
  .specs-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
  .vessel-photo-full { height: 300px; }
}
@media (max-width: 600px) {
  .specs-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
}
</style>
